    "author_association": "NONE",
    "body": "### Problem\n\nWhen trying to complete the following with `nixd, version: 2.9.0` (cursor at `|`):\n```\n{\n  security.|\n}\n```\n\nNeovim prints:\n\n```\nvim.schedule callback: ...-fd1e019e9/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua:264: attempt to get length of a userdata value                           \nstack traceback:                                                                                                                                            \n        ...-fd1e019e9/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua:264: in function 'get_doc'                                                              \n        ...-fd1e019e9/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua:446: in function '_lsp_to_complete_items'                                               \n        ...-fd1e019e9/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua:572: in function '_convert_results'                                                     \n        ...-fd1e019e9/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua:975: in function 'callback'                                                             \n        ...-fd1e019e9/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/completion.lua:599: in function 'handler'                                                              \n        ...pped-fd1e019e9/share/nvim/runtime/lua/vim/lsp/client.lua:731: in function ''                                                                     \n        vim/_core/editor.lua: in function <vim/_core/editor.lua:0>\n```\n\n### Steps to reproduce\n\n```\n$ cd (mktemp -d)\n$ nvim --clean\n:lua vim.lsp.config('nixd', { cmd = { 'nixd' }})\n:lsp enable nixd\n:e test.nix\ni{<CR>}<Esc>O  security.<C-X><C-O>\n```\n\n### Expected behavior\n\nWorking lsp completion.\n\n### Nvim version (nvim -v)\n\nNVIM v0.12.0-dev-fd1e019e9\n\n### Vim (not Nvim) behaves the same?\n\nN/A\n\n### Operating system/version\n\nNixOS 26.05pre962836.c06b4ae3d659 (Yarara)\n\n### Terminal name/version\n\ntmux 3.6a\n\n### $TERM environment variable\n\ntmux-256color\n\n### Installation\n\ncustom nixpkgs overlay",
